    },
    {
      "id": "e7557311_c29f7dfe",
      "file_path": "error-catalog-lib/src/main/kotlin/org/onap/ccsdk/error/catalog/service/ErrorCatalogService.kt",
      "patchset_number": 17,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "We should not return a nullable object here. if we can't find the error in the repository we should return an empty object saying \"unable to find the error\". Otherwise every time it gets called we need to check for null. If the object is null the logic will probably be \"unable to find the error\" anyway (or we just swallow and it's even worst). Why not put this logic at one place so we don't have to do it everywhere else we want to use the error catalog.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5732,
        "name": "Sebastien Premont-Tendland",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sebastien.premont@bell.ca",
        "username": "spremont"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-26 22:15:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "36981a97_450bba7e",
      "file_path": "error-catalog-lib/src/main/kotlin/org/onap/ccsdk/error/catalog/service/ErrorMessagesLibDBService.kt",
      "patchset_number": 17,
      "line": 73,
      "message": "use string interpolation, much easier to read than + and plus. We should consider returning the object instead because it seems like we have two meaning \"cause\" and \"action\". We should not bury that information in a string otherwise it makes it hard retrieve that after. We should format it only when we want to log it (toString override?)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5732,
        "name": "Sebastien Premont-Tendland",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sebastien.premont@bell.ca",
        "username": "spremont"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-26 22:15:58.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
